{"ID":270348, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"348\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs347.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs349.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 348<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">and it will exalt him in glory.<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> He will then take a higher exaltation, and I will take his place, and\n  thereby become exalted myself.<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> So that Jesus treads in the tracks of his Father, and inherits what\n  God did before;<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> and God is thus glorified<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> and exalted in the salvation and exaltation of all his\n  children.<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> It is plain beyond disputation, and you thus learn some of the first principles of the\n  Gospel,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> about which so much hath been said.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\"><i>When you climb up a ladder, you must begin at the bottom, and ascend step by step, until you<\/i>\n  <i>arrive at the top; and so it is with the principles of the Gospel&mdash;you must begin with the first, and<\/i>\n  <i>go on until you learn all the principles of exaltation. But it will be a great while after you have<\/i>\n  <i>passed through the veil<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> before you will have learned them. It is not all<\/i> to be comprehended in this\n  world; it will be a great work to learn our salvation<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> <i>and exaltation even beyond the grave.<\/i> I suppose\n  I am not allowed to go into an investigation of anything that is not contained in the Bible. If I do,\n  I think there are so many over-wise<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> men here, that they would cry &ldquo;treason&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and put me to death.<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span>\n  So I will go to the old Bible and turn commentator today.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Meaning of the Hebrew Scriptures<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">I shall comment on the very first Hebrew word in the Bible;<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> I will make a comment on the\n  very first sentence of the history of the creation in the Bible&mdash;<i>Berosheit.<\/i> I want to analyze the word.\n  <i>Baith<\/i>&mdash;in, by, through, and everything else. <i>Rosh<\/i>&mdash;the head. <i>Sheit<\/i>&mdash;grammatical termination. When\n  the inspired man wrote it, he did not put the <i>baith<\/i> there. An old Jew without any authority added the\n  word; he thought it too bad to begin to talk about the head!  It read first, &ldquo;The head one of the Gods\n  brought forth the Gods.&rdquo;  That is the true meaning of the words. <i>Baurau<\/i> signifies to bring forth. If\n  you do not believe it, you do not believe the learned man of God.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> Learned men can teach you no\n  more than what I have told you. <i>Thus the head God brought forth the Gods in the grand council.<\/i><span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I will transpose and simplify it in the English language. Oh, ye lawyers, ye doctors, and ye\n  priests,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> who have persecuted me, I want to let you know that the Holy Ghost knows something as\n  well as you do.<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> The head God called together the Gods and sat in grand council<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> to bring forth the\n  world. The grand councilors sat at the head in yonder heavens and con-<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106513\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106513)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106513)\">1 Chr. 29:11<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106746\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106746)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106746)\">Ps. 57:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116379\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116379)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116379)\">D&amp;C 132:19,31,57<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116738\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116738)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116738)\">Moses 1:37-39<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108659\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108659)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108659)\">John 3:35<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116411\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116411)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116411)\">D&amp;C 132:31<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108815\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108815)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108815)\">John 14:28<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116739\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116739)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116739)\">Moses 1:39<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110166\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110166)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110166)\">Heb. 5:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110176\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110176)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110176)\">Heb. 6:1-2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110242\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110242)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110242)\">Heb. 10:20<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108426\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108426)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108426)\">Luke 1:77<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112208\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112208)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112208)\">Alma 37:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112239\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112239)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112239)\">Alma 38:9<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112550\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112550)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112550)\">3 Ne. 5:20<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116137\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116137)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116137)\">D&amp;C 128:11<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106987\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106987)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106987)\">Eccl. 7:16<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111196\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111196)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111196)\">2 Ne. 9:28,42<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111285\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111285)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111285)\">2 Ne. 28:15<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">10. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106535\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106535)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106535)\">2 Chr. 23:13<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">11. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107369\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107369)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107369)\">Jer. 26:15<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107412\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107412)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107412)\">Jer. 38:15<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">12. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"105946\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 105946)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(105946)\">Gen. 1:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">13. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106351\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106351)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106351)\">Deut. 33:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">14. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115788\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115788)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115788)\">D&amp;C 121:32<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">15. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111965\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111965)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111965)\">Alma 14:18,27<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">16. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108855\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108855)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108855)\">John 16:13-15<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115768\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115768)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115768)\">D&amp;C 121:26<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">17. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117061\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117061)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117061)\">Abr. 4:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n<\/div>"}